                <pb facs="0662" n="640" xml:id="pg_640"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Records of Previous Meetings</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council approved the records of its 19th, 20th, 21st and 22nd Meetings.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Newt Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed to hold a private meeting on the same day at 9:45 p.m., in the
                    office, and under the chairmanship of Mr. Byrnes.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Further Work of the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed that the Deputies would examine the questions still outstanding in
                    the draft treaty with Finland and report to the Council.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Draft Treaty With Roumania</hi>. (<gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M. (D) (46)</gloss> 182).<note n="35" xml:id="d207fn35">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Danube</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views on the texts proposed by the U.K. Delegation (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss> 148)<note n="36" xml:id="d207fn36">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_629">p. 629</ref>.</note> and
                    by the Soviet Delegation (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.(46)</gloss>
                        135),<note n="37" xml:id="d207fn37">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_613">p. 613</ref>.</note> the
                    Council decided to adjourn the discussion of this question.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Restitution</hi> (Art. 23 and Appendix I, Part II, 1,
                        2)<note n="38" xml:id="d207fn38">Appendix I of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 182 is printed separately as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 139, June 5, 1946, <ref target="#pg_474">p. 474</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Referred back to the Deputies for further discussion on the wording proposed by
                    the Soviet Delegation namely: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Roumanian Government and the Government entitled to restitution may
                            conclude agreements to take the place of the provisions of the present
                            article”,</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">to be inserted after the text proposed by the U.S. Delegation
                    and contained in para. 1 of Part II.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">United Nations</hi> (Appendix II, Part 111, 5.)<note n="39" xml:id="d207fn39">Appendix II of <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D)
                            (46)</gloss> 182 is not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Economic Committee to submit a report on this question
                    by 27th June.</p>
                <p>4. <hi rend="italic">General economic clauses</hi>. (Article 33.)<note n="40" xml:id="d207fn40">Article 33 is not printed, but see footnote 34, <ref target="#pg_637">p. 637</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, the Council decided to adjourn the discussion of this
                    question.</p>
